Ill be sharing a few clips from the panel I spoke on this past weekend for those who couldn’t make it! The question for this specific clip was “How do you balance relationships/love life and work/ being an entrepreneur?” The beginning of my answer was in response to someone who suggested not to date/ be in a relationship because of their past experiences which is totally understandable. I personally am all about being intentional, dating with a purpose, and not playing games at this grown age so for whoever finds me will be able to reciprocate that and create a healthy balance.

1950s-60s film @colorofautumnfilm styled by me (lead costume designer) and assistant styling (assistant costume designer) by my girl @heychelseamari 

This was such a challenging project for me. I had over 20 cast (adults and children) to fit and style for this film. I only two weeks to prep and It was a three day set. The era of wardrobe is what made it more difficult. I had to do a lot of thrifting and research. @heychelseamari was a huge help being that she loves that era of fashion, she saved me lol! This film is super powerful and the team was amazing! It’s most definitely my favorite project so far! I’m excited for you all to see it soon❤️ thank you @colorofautumnfilm  for such an unforgettable experience 🙏🏾

@larussell Styled by me ✨One of the biggest lessons I’ve learned as a stylist is to always make the client feel comfortable no matter how much you think you right, it ain’t about you! Stylist often think we know what’s best when it comes to wardrobe and we try to force someone into clothes WE like. That’s not how it works. Believe it or not, it was challenging to style my guy @larussell lol but I loved the challenge! The task was to allow him to stay true to himself while elevating his style, and the catch was I could only use crocs lol 

How did he like it? HE LOVED IT! Now I’m his stylist 🙏🏾 so with that being said if you’re a brand with some 🔥🔥designs (not just T shirts and hoodies) please hit me up! We might can work something out 🤝🏽❤️

Back and I’m better 😊 I took 30 days away from social Media as a mental break and to focus on what’s important to me with no distractions. I needed to be intentional with God and wheew what a journey but it was so Amazing I almost didn’t come back to social media lol the peace I found is inexplainable ❤️

Here’s a post of some of the things I did and celebrated while I was away! Enjoy! Lol 

1. I worked with Lauren Hill twice 
2. I took a Solo trip to Vegas to go see Usher and a had a blast by myself! I made some cousins by the end of the night 😂
3. Found out my guy @larussell threw me in a song and it went Viral.
4. Styling dope projects with amazing people 
5. I gave my 4th and 5th grade fashion students a chance to style real models and they ATE DOWN!
6. Continuing to teach my Fashion enrichment class at EOYDC❤️
7. Being a mentor and teaching me mentee how to be a stylist!
8. Supporting my daughter at her dance performances 
9. I have a 10 yr old 🥹 and celebrated her evolving into a young lady.
10. Took my daughter to see The Lion King Play 10/10 show! 
11. Realizing that I worked so hard to grow my businesses, that they are flourishing with out social media. I was booked and blessed! 

There’s so much more that I’ll share with time but I encourage everyone to challenge themselves to a 30 day mental break from social media and just enjoy life! Be intentional with yourself and God. Love yourself and the people around you! Find genuine peace! This app will be here lol HI YALL😊! Lol

My Fashion enrichment class at @eoydc has been so fulfilling. I am truly Living an abundant life. Living out my dreams use to make me feel I’ve succeeded in life, until I began to walk in my purpose. I am more fulfilled than I’ve ever been. Find your “why” and live for that! 

 🎥 @artbyblack

I’ve went back and forth about posting this video but I wouldn’t feel like I’m fully my duty as an educator, parent, and adult if I didn’t. I want to bring awareness to adults because children need to be guided! They need to be taught! They need to be loved. Don’t let social media raise your kids. He present in these babies lives. Educators, always take moments like these as teachable. We are always so quick to reprimand and punish instead of teach to grow. This made me so sad and I was speechless at first and didn’t know what to say but now I’m holding my self accountable as well ti do better for the babies❤️
